A vintage 1960s travel poster style illustration featuring a stylized map of Southeast Asia with three glowing pin points marking Jakarta, Seoul, and Hanoi, connected by sweeping golden dotted flight paths arcing across the composition. The map uses warm retro colors—burnt orange, teal, and cream—with subtle paper texture. Small iconic architectural silhouettes rise from each city location: a traditional Indonesian temple, a Korean pagoda, and a Vietnamese pagoda. The sky above fades into a gradient of amber and dusty rose, suggesting adventure and movement across the region. The entire image has that classic mid-century modern aesthetic with bold shapes and limited color palette.
